{"key":"processedPost-9022806","value":{"id":9022806,"first":9021646,"last":9023707,"when":1223047389,"utime":"10/03/08 06:23 PM","content":"Calcium carbonate(ground limestone) is of little benefit to casing layers because by the time it goes to work in a few weeks, the lifespan of your casing layer is already passed.<br /><br />You want hydrated lime, and you want to use it no more than one teaspoon of lime per cup of peatmoss unless you have a way of testing pH.<br /><br />Gypsum is used for totally different reasons and will alter pH very little.&nbsp; I'd suggest using gypsum at up to 10% of the amount of peat by volume.<br />RR","title":"Re: Calcium Carbonate"}}